#Install
##Python part
+ Make sure you have installed python 3.4 [https://www.python.org/downloads/] and pip 
+ Download [https://github.com/darka91/DataHiding/archive/master.zip]
+ Unzip
> unzip DataHiding-master.zip
+ Go into code directory 
> cd DataHiding-master/Code/
+ Install requirements make sure that pip3 works for python3.4 with 
+ Install Pillow external libraries 
>(mac os) brew install libtiff libjpeg webp little-cms2
>(linux) sudo apt-get install python3.4-dev libtiff5-dev libjpeg8-dev zlib1g-dev \
    libfreetype6-dev liblcms2-dev libwebp-dev tcl8.6-dev tk8.6-dev python-tk

> sudo pip3 install -r requirements.txt
+ Install nltk
> sudo python3.4 -m nltk.downloader -d /usr/share/nltk_data all

##Matlab part
+ Matlab in command line, we require **Computer Vision System Toolbox**
> sudo ln -s /Applications/MATLAB*/bin/matlab /usr/local/bin/matlab

+ Install sqlite driver following this[https://github.com/kyamagu/matlab-sqlite3-driver]